    "body": "Use more direct 'kind' instead of indirect 'max character' calculation to determine Unicode result kind in __Pyx_PyUnicode_Join(). This avoids an indirection, seems to make the code a bit faster and modules that use a lot of f-strings are slightly smaller.\r\n\r\nFor simple f-string patterns like pure value concatenation or when texts and placeholders alternate, we can easily replace the length and kind aggregation using C loops with appropriate steps, so I've implemented that, too.\r\n\r\nI've removed the previous node result code deduplication here since I doubt that it ever had any effect. Values will usually reside in temps with distinct names, even when the values are identical.",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-04T16:13:03Z",
